<br>
at level 40: SoS/JM = 28.65 DPS <br>
                JM/SoS = 28.64 DPS<br>
<br>
This includes the 49% chance to double attack.<br>
<br>
Hmm, this is closer than I expected. Seems at 43 JM/SoS would have the advantage. However, I would like to see some parsed data over several mobs of the same type to see if this holds in reality. It should be noted tho that haste would probably improve the SoS/JM more than the JM/SoS combo. Eventually the JM/SoS will be better but for level 40 it probably doesn't matter. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ustoneglacier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stoneglacier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Master</span><br>  Posts: 540<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(5/25/02 10:48:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm6.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1527.topic&index=9>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Stave of sheilding question</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>  So.. really no reason I can think that he would want SoS primary.  <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
